<Base title="SocialProof for General Contractors — Testimonials That Overcome Bid Hesitation | SocialProof" description="General contractors: win more bids with client testimonials that prove your workmanship, reliability, and communication. Free to start.">
  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for General Contractors
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Homeowners hiring a general contractor are making a five- or six-figure decision. They're nervous. They've heard horror stories. Your testimonials from satisfied clients are the single most powerful tool in your bid — more than your license, your price, or your brochure.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Why GC reviews matter more than most</h2>
      <p>General contractors run larger, longer projects than most home service businesses. The stakes are high: clients are living in disruption for weeks or months. They need to trust that you'll deliver on time, manage subs effectively, stay on budget, and clean up after yourself. Testimonials that speak to all four win bids.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">The testimonials that close bids</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Timeline honesty:</strong> "They told us 8 weeks and finished in 7. On a project this size, that never happens."</li>
        <li><strong>Budget integrity:</strong> "One minor change order the whole project. Everything else was exactly what was quoted."</li>
        <li><strong>Sub management:</strong> "Never had to chase anyone. They coordinated everything — we just watched it happen."</li>
        <li><strong>Communication:</strong> "Daily updates. We always knew what was happening and what was next."</li>
        <li><strong>Quality finish:</strong> "The craftsmanship is beautiful. We get compliments every time someone visits."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">How SocialProof works for contractors</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Send after project completion</strong> — when clients are excited and relieved, not mid-chaos.</li>
        <li><strong>Embed on your website</strong> — homepage, project gallery, contact page.</li>
        <li><strong>Include in bid packets</strong> — link your testimonial page in every proposal you send.</li>
        <li><strong>Build by project type</strong> — kitchen remodels, additions, whole-home renovations each get their own story.</li>
      </ol>

      <div style="background:#f0f7ff;border-radius:12px;padding:2rem;margin-top:2.5rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Win more bids with proof</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Free forever for 1 active widget. No credit card required.</p>
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/register" style="background:#2563eb;color:white;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:8px;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;font-size:1rem;">Start Free</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
